                            The premise that Nehru was the "founder" of the IITs is a myth. The IITs were set up based on the recommendations of a pre-independence technical committee established by Viceroy Lord Wavell, and Nehru was not on that committee and had nothing to do with it. In any event, Nehru died in 1964 when the first batch of engineers had just graduated from *one* IIT, and the other IITs were still under construction. Nehru had nothing to do with shaping the IIT curriculum or scholastic structure.<br/><br/>
If the Humanities departments at the IITs are still labouring under the misconception that Nehru "founded" the IITs, then it's probably a very good idea to dispense with them.
